      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>As shown in Figure 23.5, the Claisen reaction is reversible. That is, a <i>β</i>-keto ester can be cleaved by base into two fragments. Using curved arrows to indicate electron flow, show the mechanism by which this cleavage occurs.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcFlZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--9ca6aab3ae34932cd5bb8ff11378ac229ccacd9b/OChem_23_07_004.jpg\" alt=\"Ethyl benzoylacetate reacts with sodium hydroxide and ethanol, forming benzoate ion and ethyl acetate.\">",
